            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-[#7C3AED] font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Low overhead numbers decrease donations</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">A/B tested homepage: "95% goes to programs" vs transparent breakdown including salaries, rent, software. <strong class="text-[#7C3AED]">Transparent version: 27% higher donation rate.</strong> Donors know organizations need infrastructure. Pretending to be 100% efficient feels dishonest. Transparency builds trust; "perfect" numbers raise suspicion.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-[#7C3AED] font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Individual stories beat statistics</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Homepage A: "We've helped 10,000 people." Homepage B: Story about Maria, single mother of 3, who found housing. <strong class="text-[#7C3AED]">Homepage B generated 3x more donations.</strong> Statistics describe scale, stories create connection. Donors give to people, not numbers. One specific story > 1000 general statistics.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-[#7C3AED] font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Volunteer signups outpace donor signups 4:1</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Added "Volunteer" and "Donate" buttons side-by-side. For every 1 donor signup, got 4 volunteer signups. Tested again with donate-first placement: 3 volunteers per donor. <strong class="text-[#7C3AED]">Volunteers are easier to acquire than donors.</strong> But volunteers often become donors later (42% conversion after 6 months). Volunteer pipeline is donor development.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

