        <div class="bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE PROBLEM</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Donate button hidden. $800/month. Mission impact: limited.</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Asked: "Where's your donate button?" Director: "In the navigation, second link from left." Checked: yes, there. Small text, same color as other links. No urgency. No prominence.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Homepage had: mission statement, program photos, volunteer opportunities, upcoming events. All important. But <strong class="text-red-700">donateâ€”the one action that funds everythingâ€”wasn't a button, wasn't prominent, wasn't obvious.</strong> Visitors had to want to donate, then hunt for how.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE FIX -->
        <div class="bg-[#7C3AED]/10 border-[3px] border-[#7C3AED] p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#7C3AED] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Moved donate to top-right. Made it a button. Added to every page. Made it sticky on mobile.</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Three changes: 1) "Donate" button in header, top-right, bright color. 2) Same donate button on every page (not just homepage). 3) Mobile: donate button sticks to bottom of screen, always visible.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Same donation flow. Same payment processor. Same suggested amounts. <strong class="text-[#7C3AED]">Just made it impossible to miss.</strong> Director: "Will this look too aggressive? We don't want to seem desperate." Response: "You're a food bank. Fighting hunger isn't aggressiveâ€”it's necessary."
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE AFTER -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#7C3AED] p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#7C3AED] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-3">First month: $4,100. Previously $800. Hiring staff now.</h3>
          <p class="text-white/90 leading-relaxed">
            Month 1: $4,100 in donations (+413%). Month 2: $3,800. Month 3: $4,500. Settled around $4,200/month average. <strong class="text-[#7C3AED]">$47,000 additional annual revenue.</strong> Hired part-time program coordinator. Expanded service hours. "Younger people don't give" narrative? Wrong. They give when you make it easy.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

